appropriate /əˈprəʊprɪɪt/

1. ADJ Something that is appropriate is suitable or acceptable for a particular situation. 适当的 

例： It is appropriate that Hispanic names dominate the list. 西班牙人的名字在这个名单中占主导地位是适当的。 

例： Dress neatly and attractively in an outfit appropriate to the job. 穿适合于这份工作的整洁美观的套装。 

2. appropriately ADV 适当地 

例： Behave appropriately and ask intelligent questions. 举止要得体，提问要机智。

